<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I agree. Up to them going to Amsterdam the book was entirely serious and believable. And suddenly it jumps into a ludicrous ending which might be fine<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I agree. Up to them going to Amsterdam the book was entirely serious and believable. And suddenly it jumps into a ludicrous ending which might be fine in, say, a Howard Jacobson novel, but not in this one.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
