<span id="freeTextContainer8524592999076266464">My third Ian McEwan and another excellent read. Not quite on the level of <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6867.Atonement' title='Atonement by Ian McEwan' rel='nofollow noopener'>Atonement</a>, but still good, good enough to win the Booker Prize. It has a different feel than the other two, more of a modern day intrigue. Interesting characters, though not all that likeable, a little too elitist for me, but McEwan&apos;s storyline carries the day. The best character may be the one they buried at the beginning of the book, Molly. McEwan should write a prequel centering around her character. 4 stars.<br/><br/>1998 Booker</span>
  <span id="freeText8524592999076266464" style="display:none">My third Ian McEwan and another excellent read. Not quite on the level of <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6867.Atonement" title="Atonement by Ian McEwan" rel="nofollow noopener">Atonement</a>, but still good, good enough to win the Booker Prize. It has a different feel than the other two, more of a modern day intrigue. Interesting characters, though not all that likeable, a little too elitist for me, but McEwan's storyline carries the day. The best character may be the one they buried at the beginning of the book, Molly. McEwan should write a prequel centering around her character. 4 stars.<br /><br />1998 Booker Prize Winner. </span>
